    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Belgian barges with a gaff rig, used as market ships and primarily intended for navigation on canals. The largest types are built with a helm port transom. The mast is rigged with a long gaff that carries the gaff sail.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
